query.result:
**English:**
46 For which neither rain, nor hail, nor snow, 47 nor dew, nor frost falls higher up 48 than the short stairway of three steps;
49 thick clouds do not appear, neither sparse, 50 nor lightning, nor the daughter of Thaumas, 51 who often changes regions over there;
52 dry vapor does not rise any farther 53 than the top of the three steps of which I spoke, 54 where the vicar of Peter has his feet.
**Sanskrit:**
