106 ché riso e pianto son tanto seguaci 107 a la passion di che ciascun si spicca, 108 che men seguon voler ne’ più veraci.

query.result:
**English:**
103 Virgil turned to me with these words, 104 with a face that, though silent, said, ‘Be quiet’; 105 but virtue cannot always do what it wants;
106 for laughter and tears are so closely linked 107 to the passion that each person feels, 108 that even the most truthful people are swayed by their emotions.
